Distributed Hotel Booking Application using Python RPC
Theory (Exam Writing)
Introduction

A distributed system consists of multiple computers communicating over a network.

In a Distributed Hotel Booking System:

Client machines send requests
Server manages hotel room booking information

The communication is performed using:

RPC (Remote Procedure Call)
What is RPC?

RPC allows a client to call functions on a remote server as if they were local functions.

In this application:

Client requests room booking/cancellation
Server processes request
Result is returned to client
Problem Statement

Design and develop a distributed Hotel Booking System where a customer can:

Book room for a guest
Cancel booking of a guest

The server maintains booking records.

System Architecture
+------------+        RPC Request        +------------+
|   Client   | -----------------------> |   Server   |
|            |                          |            |
| Book Room  | <----------------------- | Booking DB |
| Cancel     |                          |            |
+------------+       RPC Response       +------------+
